    23	
    24	- This rollout's stable brief for Smitch was quiet, evidence-based, and intentional: science x soul, calm self-directed change, and an LP image that should feel editorial rather than flashy [Task 1]
    25	- The preferred composition was a 16:9 landscape image at `1792x1024` with the subject weighted to the right and generous left-side negative space reserved for later headline overlay [Task 1]
    26	- The positive visual language was specific: editorial asymmetry, soft diffused winter window light from upper-left, matte wood/paper textures, and an uncluttered desk / journal / mug scene [Task 1]
    27	- The exclusion set should be treated as hard constraints, not soft suggestions: no purple gradients, no tech-bro neon / cyberpunk, no visible typography, no laptop or phone, no people / eye contact, no symmetry, no streak or gamification motifs, and no startup-hero rounded-card grid [Task 1]
